 vi er. Vi har bl.a. vores eget økologiske brand: ØGO. Og det er naturligvis til gode Netto-priser.\n\nFlere jobs\n\nSalgsleder - København V\n\nSalg - Generelt\n\nNetto logo\n\nKøbenhavn V\n\n\n Deltid\n\n\nSouschef - København V\n\nSalg - Generelt\n\nNetto logo\n\nKøbenhavn V\n\n\n Fuldtid','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4260007488/','2025-07-01',NULL,NULL,'[\"Butiksledelse\", \"Detailhandel\", \"Detailsalg\", \"Håndtere\", \"Kundefokuseret service\", \"Kundeoplevelse\", \"Lagerstyring\", \"Merchandising\", \"Problemløsning\", \"Samarbejde\"]',NULL,'2025-07-01 10:33:29','2025-07-01 10:33:29'),(577,4252502504,'Lead React Developer',270,'København, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nLead React Developer – Shape the future of our frontend architecture\n\n📍 Copenhagen HQ | 🌍 Hybrid (up to 3 days remote) | 🚀 High-impact role in a modern tech environment\n\n\n\n\nDo you want to take the lead on frontend architecture in a modern React setup – and influence both tech direction and team culture across countries?\n\n\n\n\nWe’re looking for an experienced Lead React Developer to take ownership of the frontend in our new insurance platform. This role combines technical vision, hands-on coding, and close collaboration with other frontend developers in Denmark and Poland.\n\n\n\n\nYou’ll join a growing development department of 20+ people and work closely with other architects and lead developers. You’ll be reporting to our Head of Development, Lars Rye Petersen.\n\n\n\n\nYour role – build, lead, inspire\n\n\n\n\nAs our new frontend lead, you’ll:\n\n\n\n\nDefine and drive the technical vision for our frontend architecture\nBuild shared components and align frontend efforts across multiple teams\nGuide and mentor frontend colleagues through reviews, sessions, and sparring\nImprove the developer experience and raise the bar for frontend quality\nStay close to code while working strategically with our product and design teams\n\n\n\n\nOur applications are used by insurance professionals – from policy sales and admin to claim handling and medical assistance.\n\n\n\n\nTech stack & tools\n\n\n\n\nFrontend: React, TypeScript, Material UI (MUI), React Hook Form, Apollo Client\nBackend: .NET with GraphQL API\nTools: GitHub (with Copilot), Azure, Jira, Confluence, Figma, Storybook\nTesting: Playwright (optional: Cucumber/Gherkin)\n\n\n\n\nWhat we’re looking for\n\n\n\n\nYou’re an experienced React developer who enjoys taking ownership and creating structure. \n\nIdeally, you:\n\n\n\n\nAre an expert in React and TypeScript\nUnderstand frontend architecture and modern design patterns\nAre comfortable evaluating tools and turning vision into actionable steps\nCommunicate clearly with both tech and non-tech stakeholders\nCare deeply about code quality, UI/UX, and frontend best practices\nEnjoy supporting and inspiring other developers\n\n\n\n\nBonus if you’ve worked with Figma, Storybook, automated tests (Playwright), or design systems.\n\n\n\n\nWhy join us\n\n\n\n\nA lead role with real influence and ownership\nNo legacy code – modern architecture and clean setup\nFlexible work setup: up to 3 remote days per week\nCentrally located office in Østerbro, Copenhagen, with rooftop views\nInternational team with colleagues in Denmark, Poland, Canada, and more\nSupport for personal growth: training, reviews, knowledge sharing\nRecently certified as a Great Place to Work (Dec 2024)\nGlobal expansion journey – including North America and Asia/Pacific\nOpportunity to explore and help implement AI features as part of our evolving platform\n\n\n\n\nInterested? Let’s talk\n\n\n\n\nRecruitment is handled by iHeadHunt. For more info, reach out to:\n\n📧 Marle – mk@iheadhunt.dk\n\n📞 +358 50 336 1636\n\n\n\n\nWe review applications continuously – so don’t wait too long to get in touch.','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4252502504/','2025-06-17',100,NULL,'[\".NET\", \"GraphQL\", \"React.js\", \"TypeScript\", \"Designmønstre\", \"Gherkin\", \"GitHub Copilot\", \"Material-UI\", \"Microsoft Azure\", \"React Hooks\", \"Sammenfald\"]',NULL,'2025-07-01 10:33:34','2025-07-01 10:33:34');
